details.description: The Coffeeshop, located in Cornelius, NC, is a cozy, family-owned spot known for its high-quality coffee and welcoming vibe. We’ve partnered with NightSwim Roaster in Charlotte to bring you the freshest, locally roasted beans, and we offer a selection of delicious baked goods from The Bakery Shop in Huntersville. Whether you're grabbing a quick coffee, settling in to work with our free WiFi, or enjoying a snack, The Coffeeshop is the perfect place to relax and recharge.

Love meeting up here! Delicious coffee & great staff.  Decor is cozy & cool, conveniently located in downtown Cornelius with plenty of parking on street & in back of shop! My favorite local coffee shop!
Cozy coffee shop with friendly staff and great coffee. Indoor and outdoor areas. Check it out!

I love this coffee shop! My service dog and I go there every Saturday and Sunday before or after our morning walk on the lake. The staff is always so friendly!  Rachel is so sweet and Bobbi (my dog) loves seeing here because he knows he will get his pup cup! They were so welcoming to Bobbi. Bobbi is a pittie, so we are often not welcomed in many establishments even as a service animal but they were so welcoming and kind to Bobbi! Their coffee is also amazing and their pastries. I also love that they have events with food trucks so sometimes you can get a full brunch meal with your coffee! I love also coming during the week and working there with my dog! They also have an amazing shop next door that is dog friendly as well! Love this place!

Chai tea latte tasted horrible.  I watched them make it, but it smelled bad and tasted like it was spoiled.  The staff was a little less than friendly, but they were quick.  Was in a hurry, so didn't take it back.  Maybe it was just a bad day, but probably won't return for the cost and risk it might be bad again.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Oh no, we hate to hear that. That is definitely not the standard we strive for. Please come back by for a Chai Tea on us!

So the cocktails are absolutely perfect, great bartenders. The atmosphere is like they bought a bunch of stuff on temu and it's all just the wrong size and the lights are just the wrong color temperature and to everyone claiming it's a great date spot, let's be real, no one is flattering in children sized chairs and spotlighted booths that are higher than the children size chairs.

It is a cocktail bar, doesn't need bright spotlights raking down the faces of people trying to cozy up on a date.

We only stayed for one before heading out to a cozier spot. I hope they can find adult size chairs soon.

reviews_data.review_text: The first time came here and our very first impression is a big disappointment. We came for a Cinco de Mayo and there was a sign on the table for $10 Margaritas. We ordered two and the bill came as $28. When I asked the reason for the price, the young lady told me that they run out of house tequila and made a margarita with different tequila but I saw all the filling of our drink and it was not specially made and it filled the premade tank. Also, even if that was the case, she should have informed us about the pricing when we are ordering in the first place. Not an honest business/ employee. It was our first and officially the last time in that place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Oh no so sorry that happened. You are correct the price change should have been relayed. Please come by and grab a $25 gift for the miscommunication. We got extremely busy for the social district event and overwhelmed the staff a bit. Please come back on a normal day and enjoy one of our fantastic craft cocktails! If you could please email us at info@thigslkn.com and let us know when you will be by to grab your gift card.

reviews_data.review_text: If 0 stars were an option then this place would have it. I've been there 3 times and each one has come with an issue with them charging more than what's on the menu. Do not get fleeced by their staff, check your receipts.

Also Long Island Ice Teas which is what you ordered is not on our menu and due to us being a craft Cocktail Bar we do not carry bottom of the barrel liquor which means a Long Island Ice Tea (which calls for 3oz of liquor) will be more than at a chain restaurant.

reviews_data.review_text: Came here last month and had a good time.  Server came and took my card to start a tab, I signed my name and the total ended up being $55. We participated in gingerbread decorating and those didn’t end up being on my tab but I assumed that was because no one else participated and no prize was won (it was advertised to be this whole gingerbread competition and it ended up being just us doing it) This whole past month I’ve been calling and leaving messages because they charged me 3 times, all different prices each time. The only people with me were my mom and sister and we all left at the same time so I know they did not add anything to my tab after I left. Since they never would answer my calls I fought with my bank for my money back. They said they could not give it to me and provided me with photos of the receipts from thigs showing I signed all of them. The $55 you can clearly see is my signature, the other one is a curved line. I clearly was not the one who signed those. Not sure what to do since no one will pick up the phone or call me back from the messages I have left.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Katie we are sorry to hear you have a discrepancy with your tab. Let's see if we can help. If you could please contact us one of several ways. Go to www.thigslkn.com and fill out the contact us form or dm us via instagram or facebook and if those don't work please email info@thigslkn.com or geoff@thigslkn.com. We will do our best to resolve the issue. Also for the phone we don't open until 5 pm and we are usually busy helping customers. As for the vm being left and not response, we apologize that should not happen and we will handle that issue in house. Please contact us asap via the routes listed above and we will get your issue resolved. Thank you management!

reviews_data.review_text:
My friends and I went to visit this location as we were wanting a refreshing cocktail after being in the sun for sometime for the festival down the street. I walked in first with a stroller of my 5 month old niece and immediately the staff starts SCREAMING from behind the bar that no one under 21 is allowed in the bar. I’m taken back by this and I respond with, it’s a baby….

They start yelling back, again from behind the bar creating a scene that no one under 21 is allowed in the bar. Ok, if that’s your rule then fine but don’t start screaming at my friends and I to get out because we have a baby. There is a different way to handle the situation like, politely coming over to me stating the situation. Staff was rude and unprofessional.

I won’t be back. Baby or no baby.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Alexandria we take our reviews serious whether its a 1 star or 5 star and we appreciate them all. We try and celebrate with our team when we get a 5 star and we speak with the staff anytime we receive anything less than a 5 star to continuously work on making our location better for the community. After reviewing your review with our staff we are disappointed we were unable to relay the message of being 21 and up in a better manner. We posted it on the front door and windows to try and prevent anyone under 21 entering. We do understand sometimes those signs can be over looked. Our staff is instructed by ownership & NC law to be strict on the age of individuals entering our establishment. We definitely do not instruct our staffs to scream at anyone. After speaking with the staff they said you had entered as we had just gotten our first wave from the festival and all employees were busy crafting cocktails. The employee who first let you know you had to be 21+ to enter said you responded and said that a random gentleman outside said it was ok to enter. So the GM said he spoke up and let you know that you had to be 21+ to enter but we could help you at the door and bring your drink to you. He did say the music was loud and there was several patrons in the building at the time and he did speak up to make sure you heard him but he was in no way trying to scream at you. We apologize and would like another opportunity to earn your business and a 5 star review! If you would like to discuss the issue further please feel free to email ownership at info@thigslkn.com.

reviews_data.review_text: If you havent been here yet, youre missing out! It is a smaller location, which makes the overall atmosphere a bit more intimate. reviews_data.review_text:
Updating my review based on the last 3 times I’ve been to Thigs.

I have spent the past 4-5 months regularly swinging by Thigs with friends and family for cocktails. However, the past month the vibes have 180 degrees changed. The staff are always cleaning up giving the vibes they want you to leave, music is either too loud or not working, lights are always too bright, cocktails still fab but no heart behind the presentation anymore…list go on and on.

It makes me sad but I don’t feel comfortable going here anymore.

—————

Thigs is an understated classy, chic cocktail bar in LKN open until midnight. Delicious craft cocktails on the menu or bartenders will create a concoction to your taste preferences.

Live music, fun bartenders, sexy ambiance, good vibes all around.

Spent my NYE here and had a blast, loved the late night dancing!

Thank you Thigs for crushing the cocktail scene, providing a cool space to bring visitors and offering a chill place to hang late night.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Updated Reply! Beth we again appreciate you updating us on your review. We work very had to create a great atmosphere and when we do not live up to that we reach out and ask for our customers to email us at info@thigslkn.com and let us know how we fell short and what we could do to make your experience great the next time you come in. We look forward to hearing from you!

Beth we greatly appreciate those kind words and extremely happy you enjoyed our NYE party. We hope to see you again soon. Cheers!!!

raw_data.name: The Coffeeshop
raw_data.description: The Coffeeshop, located in Cornelius, NC, is a cozy, family-owned spot known for its high-quality coffee and welcoming vibe. We’ve partnered with NightSwim Roaster in Charlotte to bring you the freshest, locally roasted beans, and we offer a selection of delicious baked goods from The Bakery Shop in Huntersville. Whether you're grabbing a quick coffee, settling in to work with our free WiFi, or enjoying a snack, The Coffeeshop is the perfect place to relax and recharge.

reviews_data.review_text: The first time came here and our very first impression is a big disappointment. We came for a Cinco de Mayo and there was a sign on the table for $10 Margaritas. When I asked the reason for the price, the young lady told me that they run out of house tequila and made a margarita with different tequila but I saw all the filling of our drink and it was not specially made and it filled the premade tank. Also, even if that was the case, she should have informed us about the pricing when we are ordering in the first place. Not an honest business/ employee. It was our first and officially the last time in that place.

reviews_data.review_text: Came here last month and had a good time.  Server came and took my card to start a tab, I signed my name and the total ended up being $55. We participated in gingerbread decorating and those didn’t end up being on my tab but I assumed that was because no one else participated and no prize was won (it was advertised to be this whole gingerbread competition and it ended up being just us doing it) This whole past month I’ve been calling and leaving messages because they charged me 3 times, all different prices each time. The only people with me were my mom and sister and we all left at the same time so I know they did not add anything to my tab after I left. Since they never would answer my calls I fought with my bank for my money back. They said they could not give it to me and provided me with photos of the receipts from thigs showing I signed all of them. The $55 you can clearly see is my signature, the other one is a curved line. I clearly was not the one who signed those. Not sure what to do since no one will pick up the phone or call me back from the messages I have left.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Katie we are sorry to hear you have a discrepancy with your tab. Let's see if we can help. If you could please contact us one of several ways. Go to www.thigslkn.com and fill out the contact us form or dm us via instagram or facebook and if those don't work please email info@thigslkn.com or geoff@thigslkn.com. We will do our best to resolve the issue. Also for the phone we don't open until 5 pm and we are usually busy helping customers. As for the vm being left and not response, we apologize that should not happen and we will handle that issue in house. Please contact us asap via the routes listed above and we will get your issue resolved. Thank you management!

reviews_data.review_text:
My friends and I went to visit this location as we were wanting a refreshing cocktail after being in the sun for sometime for the festival down the street. I walked in first with a stroller of my 5 month old niece and immediately the staff starts SCREAMING from behind the bar that no one under 21 is allowed in the bar. I’m taken back by this and I respond with, it’s a baby….

They start yelling back, again from behind the bar creating a scene that no one under 21 is allowed in the bar. Ok, if that’s your rule then fine but don’t start screaming at my friends and I to get out because we have a baby. There is a different way to handle the situation like, politely coming over to me stating the situation. Staff was rude and unprofessional.

I won’t be back. Baby or no baby.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Alexandria we take our reviews serious whether its a 1 star or 5 star and we appreciate them all. We try and celebrate with our team when we get a 5 star and we speak with the staff anytime we receive anything less than a 5 star to continuously work on making our location better for the community. After reviewing your review with our staff we are disappointed we were unable to relay the message of being 21 and up in a better manner. We posted it on the front door and windows to try and prevent anyone under 21 entering. We do understand sometimes those signs can be over looked. Our staff is instructed by ownership & NC law to be strict on the age of individuals entering our establishment. We definitely do not instruct our staffs to scream at anyone. After speaking with the staff they said you had entered as we had just gotten our first wave from the festival and all employees were busy crafting cocktails. The employee who first let you know you had to be 21+ to enter said you responded and said that a random gentleman outside said it was ok to enter. So the GM said he spoke up and let you know that you had to be 21+ to enter but we could help you at the door and bring your drink to you. He did say the music was loud and there was several patrons in the building at the time and he did speak up to make sure you heard him but he was in no way trying to scream at you. We apologize and would like another opportunity to earn your business and a 5 star review! If you would like to discuss the issue further please feel free to email ownership at info@thigslkn.com.

reviews_data.review_text:
Updating my review based on the last 3 times I’ve been to Thigs.

I have spent the past 4-5 months regularly swinging by Thigs with friends and family for cocktails. However, the past month the vibes have 180 degrees changed. The staff are always cleaning up giving the vibes they want you to leave, music is either too loud or not working, lights are always too bright, cocktails still fab but no heart behind the presentation anymore…list go on and on.

It makes me sad but I don’t feel comfortable going here anymore.

—————

Thigs is an understated classy, chic cocktail bar in LKN open until midnight. Delicious craft cocktails on the menu or bartenders will create a concoction to your taste preferences.

Live music, fun bartenders, sexy ambiance, good vibes all around.

Spent my NYE here and had a blast, loved the late night dancing!

Thank you Thigs for crushing the cocktail scene, providing a cool space to bring visitors and offering a chill place to hang late night.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Updated Reply! Beth we again appreciate you updating us on your review. We work very had to create a great atmosphere and when we do not live up to that we reach out and ask for our customers to email us at info@thigslkn.com and let us know how we fell short and what we could do to make your experience great the next time you come in. We look forward to hearing from you!

Beth we greatly appreciate those kind words and extremely happy you enjoyed our NYE party. We hope to see you again soon. Cheers!!!
